Yellow - Intermediate

A. 4 x E3M
5 Push press starting at 70% of 1RM
6 - 8 One arm DB rows with 2s eccentric

B. 18 min AMRAP
3/2 Wall walks
9 Box step over with DB carry anyhow 60/50 cm 22,5/15 kg
18 Deadlifts 80/50 kg or 40% of 1RM
30s rest

A. Push press is about finding a good rack position which enables you to use your legs. On the OA BD rows work on the mind muscle connection. Focus on using the lat muscles. 

B. Even thou there is a 30s rest every round make sure to not rush this one from the start. Quality reps all the way through.

INTENSE MOBILITY
3 rounds of
50s Cozzack squats
25s L +25s R One arm Side plank raises
3 rounds of
15s L + 15s R Scissor squat holds
50s Diagonal dead bugs
3 rounds of
50s Elephant walks
50s Reverse Nordics
3 rounds of
50s Pass throughs prone
25s L + 25s R Quadruped leg swing
3 rounds of
50s Bridge wall walks
50s Freestanding calf raises

Black - Intense skill

A. 4 x E3,5M
3 - 20 m Handstand walk/10 - 30 Shoulder taps or Progression work
1 - 4 Barbell split snatch 

B. 14 min AMRAP
7 Handstand pushups
14 Frontrack backward lunges 50/30 kg or individual weight
7 Chest to bar pullups/Pullups

Scaled alternative
14 min AMRAP
7 Pike pushups 
14 Frontrack backward lunges 30/20 kg
7 Pullups with band/Ring rows

A. On the HS walk make sure to extend the shoulders long before starting to walk. Shoulder taps is a good option to walking for building up strength. Split snatches is a very complex movement which creates a very good foundation for other movements. Getting strong and efficient in this one tranfers to regular snatches, lunge movements, general core stability etc.

B. Intense met-con leaning a little bit more towards the upperbody. Probably break up the Hspu/Pike and CTB/Pullup variation from the start

INTENSE MOBILITY
3 rounds of
50s Back body line hold
50s Grasshopp stretches with holds
3 rounds of
50s L + 50s R Knee over toe split squats
50s Relaxed Kip swings
3 rounds of
90s Jefferson curls
50s Handstand heel pulls
2 rounds of
50s L + 50s R Diagonal stretch
50s Windshield wipers

Green - Endurance

36 x OTM
6 - 15 cal Row/Bike or Ski
15 - 30s Top ring support hold/Front leaning rest
4 - 6 L + 4 - 6 R Pistols for quality
10 - 25s L+ 10 - 25s R Star plank/Side plank hold
8 - 12 Barbell row with a supinated grip
20 - 25s L + 20 - 25s R One arm Overhead KB carry

Long endurance work with a good overall load. Make sure to stay in a more comfortable zone if this is your third workout this week or if your shooting a couple of more sessions. 	

GYMNASTICS
A. EMOM 16
2-4 Skin the cat in Bar
6-12 Hips to rings
8-12 Weighted Tuck 2 Hollow -lying down
8-12 Banded Pull Apart

B. For Time: 
21-15-9 
Toes to Bar
Burpee to target

OLY
A. EMOM x 5 
3 Muscle clean, 3 press (empty barebell)
B. E2M x 5 
2 Power Clean, 2 push jerk 80+%
C. E2M x 5 
5-4-3-2-1 Clean pull 90+%
D. E2M x 5 
5 push press 75%

Yellow - Intermediate

A. 4 x E3M
3 - 5 Sumo deadlift new set up on each rep
5 - 7 Ring pushups with 3 s eccentric

B. TEAM 
20 min AMRAP
60 Kettlebell swings american 24/16 kg (divide anyhow)
30 Situps synchronized
60 Squat jumps/Squats (divide anyhow)
30 DB Push jerk or Push press 22,5/15 kg (divide anyhow)

A. Tight core and make sure to anchor the hips before every rep. On the ring pushups make sure to keep the shoulders tight together with the core. 

B. Team workout with four different movements. Make sure to communicate all the way through and if one of you feels stronger he/she takes a bigger chunk.

Red - Intense

A. 4 x E3,5M
6 + 6 DB Bulgarian split squats 3s eccentric
4 - 6 Harop curls or Leg curl on the rower

B. "D.T"
5 rounds for time:
12 Deadlifts 70/47,5 kg 
9 Hang power cleans 
6 Push jerks
Time cap 15 min
Estimate weight from 70% of 1 RM Push jerk

A. Use DBs on the BSS and strive for hitting the front leg/glute as much as possible. Keep the tempo on both movements. Maybe stay of max effort to save some energy for "D.T"...

B. Classic "Hero" benchmark with a lot grit practice. Make sure to choose weights according to capacity and make sure to hit the correct tempo from the start. For most of us the Hang power cleans is the toughest movement, so maybe break them up from the start. This one will be nasty!

TEAM	

A. 15 min AMRAP
10 Chest to bar pullups/Pullups/Eccentric/Ring row
15 KB frontrack squats 2 x 24/16 kg or Individual weights
20 Sumo deadlift high pull 50/35 kg 

B. 15 min AMRAP
30 Wallballs 9/6 kg 3/2,7 m
15 Singel arm Devils press 22,5/15 kg
10 Power snatch 50/35 kg

Divide these two high intensity pieces anyhow. Can you move well with good technique all the way through?		

STRENGTH
A. 4 x E3M
1 - 3 Rope climbs
10 - 20m Heavy sled push
B. 4 x E3M
5 Narrow grip bench press starting at 70%
5 + 5 One leg KB deadlift with a one arm row on every rep
C. 4 x E3M
20 - 30m Heavy farmers carry
5 Sandbag/Medball over shoulder clean

2 rounds of (41 min)

400/350 m Row
4 - 8 No pushup Burpee with Box step ups 60/50 cm
8 - 16 Squats
1 min rest

1 - 3 Wall walks
1 min rest

400/350 m Row
10 - 18 Lunges alternating leg forward and back 
5 - 12 Handrelease pushups
1 min Rest

Pace it from the start to stay in the aerobic zone. Target is two rounds on each amrap while maintaining a aerobic pace. 

INTENSE MOBILITY
2 rounds of
15s L + 15s R Skater holds 
15s L + 15s R Pistol holds
15s L +  15s R Lateral Pistol holds
15s L + 15s R Contralateral Pistol holds

50s Wallfacing toe pulls/Shrugs
50s Weighted pancakes

25s L + 25s R Prone Hip CAR´s

50s Bridge reach
25s L + 25s R Standing Hip circles

A. 5 x E2M
3 Deadlifts with a new set up on each rep
directly into
3 Broad jumps
Start the DLs from 70% of 1 RM 

B. 6 min AMRAP
5 Power clean 70/45 kg or 70% of 1 RM
9 Toes to bar/15 Knee raises
45 Double unders/Singel unders 2 for 1
3 min Rest 
4 min AMRAP
5 Power clean 60/35 kg
7 Toes to bar/12 Knee raises
35 Double unders/Singel unders 2 for 1

A. Super tight set up on each DL and make sure to perform the broad jumps with control on the landings.

B. Very intense met-con which requiries a good strategy and focus from the start. Can you keep a high pace on the last rounds also?

INTENSE MOBILITY
3 rounds of
50s Hollow V-ups weighted
50s Dynamic pigeons
3 rounds of
50s Sissy squats
50s Lateral swings
3 rounds of
50s Straddle ups
50s Handstand wallfacing shoulder taps

50s Weighted shoulder complex

20 - 50s Bridge hold
15s Straddle lifts + 30s Pike lifts

Yellow - Intermediate

A. 5 x E2M
1 - 5 Hang power snatch
Build up weight starting at 60% of 1 RM

B. 50 - 40 - 30 - 20 - 10 reps for time:
Walking lunges forward and in any direction
Sit-ups (with abmat is optional)
Dumbell deadlifts 2 x 22,5/15 kg
Push press 30/20 kg or 40% of 1 RM
Time cap 24 min

A. Explosive hang power snatches with focus on control and technique. Increase the weight and decrease the reps every set if your technique is on point.

B. Long high rep intermediate met-con with four different movement patterns. Don´t rush from the start and make sure to move well all the way through.

TEAM
AMRAP 35 min (divide anyhow)
150 m Heavy Sandbag or Medball carry
100 Double unders/Singel unders 2 for 1
75 cal Row, Bike or Ski
50 Handrelease pushups
25 Dumbell thrusters 2 x 22,5/15 kg

STRENGTH
A. 4 x E3M
10 Backrack backward barbell lunges
directly into
5 - 10 High and heavy Wallballs (as high and heavy form allows)

B. 4 x E3M
5 - 10 Pushups with hands on a barbell
directly into
5 Explosive Burpee boxjumps (high)

C. 4 x E3M
5 - 10 Ring rows
directly into
20 - 40 m Heavy sandbag carry

On the Pushups make sure the barbell is not rolling and maybe use extra weight on the back. Touch the chest on the barbell every rep.

35 min (5 rounds)
20 - 30 cal Row, Ski or Bike (2 min)
10 - 20 Step ups 60/50 cm (1 min) Optional with DB
15 - 30 Sit-ups (1 min) Optional with Abmat
75 - 200 Singel unders (2 min)
15 - 45 s Supinated pullup hold/Band/Ring row hold (1 min)

Go easy today if you did yesterdays and/or mondays workout and if you want to keep this session in the aerobic zone. Transition when there is 10s left of the window. 

INTENSE MOBILITY
3 rounds of
50s Back body line pulses
25s L + 25s R Side plank rotations
3 rounds of
50s Teardrop squats
50s Pass through weighted

25s Hamstring walk outs + 25s Hip thrust hold on toes

15s L + 15s R Dragon squat hold
10 - 20s L + 10 - 20s R One arm scap pulls/Hang/Two hands

50s Russian baby makers

Yellow - Intermediate

A. 4 x E3M
4 - 6 Ring pushups with 4s eccentric
6 - 8 L + 6 - 8 R One arm Dumbell rows with 2s eccentric

B. TEAM
22 min AMRAP
24 One arm DB snatch 22,5/15 kg
18 Boxjump over 60/50 cm
12 Toes to Bar/Knee raises 2 for 1
6/3 Wall walk/Walk out to superplank

A. Best possible technique on every rep. 

B. Divide this one anyhow. Your goal is to keep moving all the way through with good technique. 

GYMNASTICS
A. 3-4  rounds
5x Hollow to support
3x Kick to Handstand - Tuck down 
5x kipped dips
8x Narrow grip PVC Overhead squats

B. E3M x 6 Alternate between B.1 and B.2 
B.1: 20x HSPU + 50x Double Unders 
(Scaled- 10-15 HSPU + 75 Single Under) 
B.2: 20M Handstand Walk + 15 Burpees 
(Scaled 6-15m HSW or 10-30 shoulder taps + 5-13 Burpees)

1 high hang snatch
1 hang snatch
1 snatch balance
B. 5xE2M
1 squat snatch
3 OHS

5xEMOM
8-10 Barbell row

Red - Intense

A. 5 x E2M
4 - 1 rep Hang power clean and jerk

B. "Karen"
For time:
150 Wallballs 9/6 kg 3/2,7 m
Time cap 12 min"	"A. Start at 70% and build the weight from there. Focus on the extension and powerful hip extension on both movements. 

B. Classic benchmark with very high intensity. Be smart from the start so you don´t make to big sets. Excpect some leg soreness tomorrow...

TEAM

A. One attempt each for as many reps as possible in unbroken sets
1. Back squat @ 1,0/0,8 x Bodyweight
2. Deadlift @ 1,5/1,2 x Bodyweight
3. Press @ 0,6/0,4 x Bodyweight
The team with the most amount of reps is the winners :-)

B. 15 min AMRAP 
15/12 cal Row each. One person working
10 Lateral burpees over rower each. One person working
20 Situps synchronized

A. Safety first and make sure to move all the way through. No pause when the set has started.

B. Fast transitions is the key.

STRENGTH
A. 4 x E3M
3 - 5 Back squats 
directly into
8 - 10 m Heavy sled drag
B. 4 x E3M
5 Push press with 1s hold on the tops
directly into
3 Broad jumps with controlled landings
C. 4 x E3M
4 - 6 Bench press with 3s eccentric
directly into
3 - 6 Pushups with clap/Fast pushups

TEAM "Murph"

For time:
1600 m Run or Row
100 Pullups/Jumping pullups/Ring row
200 Pushups/Knee pushups
300 Squats/Partial squats
1600 m Run or Row
Time cap 40 min	

In a two person team divide the run/row meters and the reps anyhow. Suggestion might be 4 x 400 m Run/Row, 10 rounds of 10 Pullups, 20 Pushups, 30 Squats and 4 x 400 Row etc. The workout starts and finishes on the same cardio movement. 

INTENSE MOBILITY
2 rounds of
50s Hollow complex
50 L + 50 R Dynamic pigeons
3 rounds of
50s Handstand floaters
50s Horse stance pulses + hold
3 rounds of
50s Arch to hollow on the bar
15s L + 15s R Contralateral squat holds
3 rounds of
50s FHL Calf raises
50s Windshield wipers
3 rounds of
30s Bridge pushups
75s Jefferson curls

Green - Endurance

A. 15 min AMRAP
150 Singel unders
20 Box step ups 60/50 cm (alternating leg)
25 Deadlifts 60/40 kg or 40% of 1RM

B. 15 min AMRAP
15 Kettlebell swing lagom 24/16 kg
20 Situps
25 Backward lunges

Two somewhat light aerobic met-cons but probably break up the DL´s on the second one. The pace on the Single unders is also very individual. Rest 1 minute btw A. and B.

Red - Intense

A. 4 x E3,5M
5 L + 5 R Knees over toes split squats with 3s eccentric 1s hold
5 L + 5 R single leg KB deadlifts alternated with one arm row

B. 7 min AMRAP
9 Toes to bar/Knee raises 2 for 1
11 Dumbell power clean 2 x 22,5/15 kg
13 Push jerk 45/30 kg
3 min Rest
5 min AMRAP
7 Toes to bar
9 Dumbell power clean 2 x 22,5/15kg
11 Push jerk 40/25 kg

A. Make sure to move forward and down on the Kot SS. Upper body stays vertical and the glute of the back leg is slightly contracted. Full R.O.M is key. On the SL KB DL keep both the core and the shoulders stable and don´t rush this movement. 

B. Two short and intense amraps. The reps and the weight on the PJ is lighter on the second one. 

GYMNASTICS
A. 3-4  rounds
5x Hollow to support
3x Kick to Handstand - Tuck down 
5x kipped dips
8x Narrow grip PVC Overhead squats

B. E3M x 6 Alternate between B.1 and B.2 
B.1: 20x HSPU + 50x Double Unders 
(Scaled- 10-15 HSPU + 75 Single Under) 
B.2: 20x Toes to Bar + 15 Burpees 

OLY
A. 5xE2M
1 power clean
3 front squat - 3 s ecc
1 split jerk
B. 5xE2M
1 Hang power clean
1 squat clean
1 jerk
C. 5xE2M
5 push press
5xEMOM
8-10 strict press

Black - Intense skill

A. 4 x E3,5M
3 - 20 m Handstand walk/Progression work
1 - 3 Rope climbs/Floor rope get ups
Scaled variation
10 - 30 Shoulder taps wallfacing/Box shoulder taps
6 - 10 Ring rows with 3s eccentric

B. 12 min AMRAP
5/3 Wall walks
7 Power snatch 60/40 kg or 70% of 1 RM
9 Burpee chest to bar pullups/Burpee pullup
Scaled variation
5 Walk out to pushup
7 Power snatch 40/25 kg
9 Burpee with a jumping pullup

A. On the HS walk make sure to extend the shoulders long before starting to walk. Shoulder taps is a good option to walking to build up strength. On the RC´s don´t stress. It´s more about using the legs by  having a good leg/feet lock.

B. High skill scalable met-con with a lot of upper body work. Scale the movements if necessary but still keep the movements somewhat challenging.

Green - Endurance

35 x OTM
8 - 14 Boxjump over 60/50 cm
40 - 50s Farmers carry KB or DB
10 - 20 m Walking lunges
10 - 20 m Bear crawl
10 - 15 Barbell rows 25 - 60 kg

Seven rounds of five different movements. Can you keep it in the green zone and somewhat more aerobic than anaerobic?

TEAM

A. 15 min AMRAP
2 L + 2 R Turkish get up 16/12 kg (synchronized)
20 Double KB russian swing 2x16/12 kg (divide anyhow)
30 Frontrack KB squat 2x16/12 kg (divide anyhow)

B. 15 min AMRAP
10 L + 10 R One arm KB snatch 16/12 kg (synchronized)
20 Handrelease pushups (divide anyhow)
30 KB backward lunges 16/12 kg (divide anyhow)

Two intense KB met-cons. Probably break up the non-synchronized movements evenly from the start and after a while be prepared to change the game plan if one of you is a bit stronger than the other. Rest 3 min btw A. and B.		

STRENGTH
A. 4 x E3M
3 - 5 Front squats starting at 75% of 1 RM
directly into 3 jumps in the stairs 3, 4 or 5 steps. Walk down btw the jumps. 
B. 4 x E3M
10 m Heavy sledpush 
directly into
15s of Split jumps high
15s of fast Burpees
C. 4 x E3M
5 Narrow grip bench press
directly into 
20 m Heavy sandbag or heavy atlasball carry

Red - Intense

A. 4 x E3,5M
3 Zombie paus squats 33x1
5 Harop curls or Leg curls on the rower with 4s eccentric

B. 5 rounds for time:
5 Thrusters 60/40 kg or 60% of 1RM
10 Power clean 
15 Handrelease pushups
Time cap 15 min

A. Use wedges under the heels or oly shoes on the Zombie squats to enable a upright sound position. A good depth is important on these ones. 

B. The thrusters should be challenging today and try to go heavier then usually if the technique feels good. 
Singels or small sets on the PC and probably break up the HR pushups from the start.

A. 5 x E2,5M
1 - 6 Bar muscle-ups/Progression work

Scaled variation

3 Pike pushups

C. 2 x

A. Use a jumping variation from a box on the B mups or work from the hang progessively higher and higher. A combination of both of them can also be used or a band variation.

B. Shoulder intense met-con with strict Hspu. This might requiere a lot of pacing from the start.

C. Make sure to roll down every vertabra and when leaning back squeeze the glutes first. On the pass throughs keep the arms straight and don´t push to hard.

3 rounds of
25s L  + 25s R One arm handstand practice/Progressions
50s Straddle ups

A. Go heavy today if the technique feels good. Safety first thou. On the Bjs make an effort to jump as high as possible on every rep. 

B. Short but intense amraps with big movements. Find your own pace and finish strong on every movement.

"Fight Gone Bad"
